The African National Congress (ANC) has appointed Sibongile Besani as head of the ANC Presidency based at Luthuli House. The appointment is effective from July 1st. The statement notes that “ANC Presidency office fulfills a critical role supporting the President and Deputy President to fulfill their responsibilities in line with Rule 16 of the Constitution of the ANC.” Besani replaces Zizi Kodwa who is the Deputy Minister of State Security. Besani served the party in various capacities, including as Provincial Secretary of the ANC in the Free State. Besani resigned as an MP to take up his new post at the party’s Luthuli House.